Get
	Raspberry Pi 3
	A HDMI display (with HDMI cable)
	A USB keyboard and mouse
	16 GB SD Card
	Power supply cable for Pi

Install Raspbian Stretch on the 16GB SD Card
	https://www.raspberrypi.org/downloads/

sudo raspi-config
	Change Password
		rfid
	Internationalisation/Localisation Options
		Change Timezone
			Asia/Kolkata
		Change Keyboard Layout
			Dell 101 Key PC, Other, English US, English US, The default for the keyboard, No compose key, No
		Wifi Country
			India
	Interfacing Options
		SSH
		SPI
	Advanced Options
		Expand filesystem
	Finish and Reboot

Setup LAN/Wifi
	Wifi - just use the GUI to connect
	LAN in Stretch is different (have to use dhcpcd.conf)
		https://www.raspberrypi.org/forums/viewtopic.php?t=191140 
	Reboot

Test SSH

sudo nano /etc/apt/apt.conf
	Acquire::http::Proxy "http://raghu:backspace@172.16.101.138:3128/";
	Acquire::https::Proxy "http://raghu:backspace@172.16.101.138:3128/";	
sudo apt-get update
nano ~/.bashrc
	#Export Proxy
	export http_proxy=http://raghu:backspace@172.16.101.138:3128/
	export https_proxy=http://raghu:backspace@172.16.101.138:3128/
source ~/.bashrc

Setup clock using htpdate
sudo apt-get install htpdate
sudo crontab -e
        * * * * * /usr/sbin/htpdate -s intranet.iitg.ernet.in

Setting up Key based SSH
Follow step 4 from here :
	https://www.digitalocean.com/community/tutorials/initial-server-setup-with-ubuntu-16-04#step-four-—-add-public-key-authentication-recommended
Disabling Password Based SSH
Follow step 5 from here :
	https://www.digitalocean.com/community/tutorials/initial-server-setup-with-ubuntu-16-04#step-five-—-disable-password-authentication-recommended

Firewall Setup
General Guides
	https://www.digitalocean.com/community/tutorials/initial-server-setup-with-ubuntu-16-04#step-seven-—-set-up-a-basic-firewall
	https://www.digitalocean.com/community/tutorials/how-to-set-up-a-firewall-with-ufw-on-ubuntu-14-04
Allow HTTP and HTTPS from everywhere
Allow SSH from required IP's
If you are going to run django development server, also allow TCP port 8000 from everywhere
Set default rule for incoming packets to deny

Clone https://github.com/krishraghuram/mess-rpisetup
Follow all instructions in "Todo" file
Complete it and Test it before continuing!!!

sudo apt-get install mariadb-server
sudo apt-get install libmariadbclient-dev
sudo mysql -u root
	CREATE DATABASE mess;
	CREATE USER 'mess'@'localhost' IDENTIFIED BY 'mess';
	GRANT ALL PRIVILEGES ON mess . * TO 'mess'@'localhost';
	FLUSH PRIVILEGES;
sudo -E -H pip install -r requirements.txt

#Clone the repo
cd ~
git clone https://github.com/krishraghuram/mess.git
cd mess
#Checkout the version(Replace x by appropriate number)
git checkout version1.x

#Test the website using django's built in webserver
cd ~/mess
python manage.py makemigrations
python manage.py migrate
python manage.py createsuperuser #Give necessary details here
python manage.py runserver 0.0.0.0:8000
